name: Unload
description: WorldEvent.Unload is fired when Minecraft unloads a world. This event is fired when a world is unloaded in Minecraft#loadWorld(WorldClient, String) , MinecraftServer.stopServer() , DimensionManager#unloadWorlds() , ForgeInternalHandler#onDimensionUnload(Unload) . This event is not Cancelable . This event does not have a result. HasResult This event is fired on the MinecraftForge#EVENT_BUS .
